The White House has sent several nominations and withdrawals to the Senate. Michael A. Botticelli has been nominated to be the Deputy Director of National Drug Control Policy. Christy L. Romero has been nominated to be the Special Inspector General for the Troubled Asset Relief Program. Alan D. Bersin has withdrawn his nomination to be the Commissioner of Customs, Department of Homeland Security. John D. Podesta has also withdrawn his nomination to be a Member of the Board of Directors of the Corporation for National and Community Service.